events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 27 points and the Boston Celtics erased an 18-point first-half deficit with a 104-92 victory over the New Orleans Pelicans on Monday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 27,  Celtics rally past Pelicans 104-92

events.name: Charlotte Hornets at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Miles Bridges made sure LaMelo Ball wasn't missed.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bridges scores 38, Hornets beat Knicks without Ball

headlines.description: — Joseph Blair was next in Washington's line of succession. With coach Wes Unseld Jr. and assistant Pat Delany in health and safety protocols, it would be his job to run the team.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kuzma, Beal lead Wizards to 117-98 rout of 76ers

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant wasn't there to make the big shot, snatch the key rebound or take over like he's done countless times.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets drop first game without Durant, fall to Cavs 114-107

headlines.description: — Desmond Bane and Ja Morant scored 25 points each, and the Memphis Grizzlies dominated the short-handed Chicago Bulls 119-106 on Monday afternoon for their 12th win in 13 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bane, Morant score 25 apiece to lead Grizzlies past Bulls

headlines.description: — Nicolas Batum scored all of his season-high 32 points in the second half, Reggie Jackson added 26 points and the Los Angeles Clippers beat the Indiana Pacers 139-133 on Monday in a matchup of sub-.500 teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Batum scores season-high 32, Clippers beat Pacers 139-133

headlines.description: — Trae Young scored 30 points for the struggling Atlanta Hawks, who trailed for much of the game before rallying for a 121-114 victory over the Milwaukee Bucks on Monday night to snap a 10-game home losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hawks rally to beat Bucks 121-114, snap 10-game home skid

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: - CJ McCollum scored 16 points in his first game back from a collapsed lung, Jusuf Nurkic added 21 points and a season-best 22 rebounds, and the Portland Trail Blazers beat the Orlando Magic 98-88 Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCollum returns, scores 16 points in Blazers' 98-88 win

headlines.description: — The final rebound of the game fell into Jimmy Butler's hands just a moment or two before the final buzzer, and Bam Adebayo started celebrating for two reasons.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bam back, Butler gets triple-double, Heat top Raptors 104-99

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 20 points, 12 assists and 11 rebounds for his third triple-double in five games, and the surging Dallas Mavericks withstood a late run by the Oklahoma City Thunder to win 104-102 Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic's triple-double leads Mavericks past Thunder 104-102

events.name: Phoenix Suns at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Devin Booker had a season-high 48 points and the Phoenix Suns dominated the fourth quarter to defeat the San Antonio Spurs 121-107 Monday night for their fourth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker's season-high 48 helps Suns rally past Spurs 121-107

events.name: Utah Jazz at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James scored 25 points and Stanley Johnson had 10 of his 15 points in the fourth quarter to lead the Los Angeles Lakers to a 101-95 win over the Utah Jazz on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron scores 25 as Lakers end three-game skid, beat Jazz
